<div class="banner dropshadow">
  <div class="fixedWidth">
    <div class="images clearfix">
      <div class="left">
        <%= image_tag "LEFT-SmartRent-Rules-252x380.jpg"%>
      </div>
      <div class="right"><%= image_tag "RIGHT-SmartRent-Rules-880x380-5.jpg"%></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="faq">
  <div class="item">
    <div class="q">
      Q:
    </div>

    <div class="qa">
      <div class="question">
        <p>What is SmartRent and why should I register?</p>
      </div>

      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: SmartRent is Bozzutoâ€™s incentive program that gives you the opportunity to earn *$350 per month credit for the time you rent 
          at <%= link_to "participating Bozzuto managed apartment properties", find_a_new_home_path %>. 
          It gives you access to automatically-accrued funds towards the purchase of a new <%= link_to "Bozzuto Home", find_a_new_home_path %>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="item">
    <div class="q">
      Q:
    </div>

    <div class="qa">
      <div class="question">
        <p>
          What is the maximum amount of money I can earn toward a 
          purchase of a new <%= link_to "Bozzuto Home", find_a_new_home_path %> by registering in the SmartRent program?
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: Renters at specific Bozzuto managed properties that participate in the SmartRent program will 
          earn $350 per month toward the purchase of 
          a new home up to a maximum of $10,000. 
          Visit the <%= link_to "Find a SmartRent Apartment", find_apartments_path %> page to see which Bozzuto properties participate in the SmartRent program.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="item">
    <div class="q">
      Q:
    </div>

    <div class="qa">
      <div class="question">
        <p>
          I have been renting at a <%= link_to "Bozzuto managed community", find_apartments_path %> for some time and it offers the SmartRent program. What happens to those funds?
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: As a Bozzuto SmartRent community resident, you automatically accrue funds. 
          Once you activate your online account on this website with the e-mail address used on your lease,
          you can view your accumulated funds in your SmartRent profile.
          You are eligible to use these funds towards the purchase of a new <%= link_to "Bozzuto Home", find_a_new_home_path %> after 12 consecutive months 
          of occupancy at a participating Bozzuto managed apartment community.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="item">
    <div class="q">
      Q:
    </div>

    <div class="qa">
      <div class="question">
        <p>
          Am I able to use a realtor in my purchase of a Bozzuto home when I use my SmartRent funds?
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: Yes. However, if you chose to use your realtor, your Smart Rent credits will be reduced by 50%.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="item">
    <div class="q">
      Q:
    </div>

    <div class="qa">
      <div class="question">
        <p>How do I know how much is in my SmartRent account?</p>
      </div>

      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: After you activate your account on this website with the e-mail address used on your lease, 
          you can access your account statement 24/7 here at <%= link_to root_url, root_url %>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="item">
    <div class="q">
      Q:
    </div>

    <div class="qa">
      <div class="question">
        <p>If the Bozzuto Homes community is offering other sales incentives, will I still be able to use my SmartRent funds?</p>
      </div>

      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          A: SmartRent funds may be used in conjunction with other promotional programs offered at certain Bozzuto Homes communities. 
          Please check with the sales manager at the <%= link_to "Bozzuto Homes", find_a_new_home_path %> community of your choice for details.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="item">
    <div class="q">
      Q:
    </div>

    <div class="qa">
      <div class="question">
        <p>Can I use my SmartRent funds as earnest money when I sign my new home sales contract?</p>
      </div>

      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          No. SmartRent funds are credited to the purchaser at the time of Deposit/Settlement and can be applied towards closing costs 
          or to reduce your monthly payments. They do not replace the required earnest money deposit funds at time of contract 
          or interim deposits due during the purchase process. 
          Please consult with the sales manager at the <%= link_to "Bozzuto Homes", find_a_new_home_path %> community of your choice for details.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="item">
    <div class="q">
      Q:
    </div>

    <div class="qa">
      <div class="question">
        <p>Can I use my SmartRent funds at any Bozzuto Homes community?</p>
      </div>

      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          Yes. However, SmartRent funds cannot be used with the purchase of a moderately priced home (MPDU) as provided through various county programs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="item">
    <div class="q">
      Q:
    </div>

    <div class="qa">
      <div class="question">
        <p>I have a roommate. Can we both participate in SmartRent?</p>
      </div>

      <div class="answer">
        <p>
          We can only allow one SmartRent participant per apartment unit. Please contact us with questions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="disclaimer">
  <p>
    * Program may vary by community. Program rules and eligibility requirements are subject to change without notice.
    By registering in the SmartRent program, you agree to receive notifications and promotions from Bozzuto Homes.
  </p>
</div>
